# {{CMD_PREFIX}}-sync

Model/effort: Sonnet / medium.

The close ritual, invoked directly. Captures everything that changed this session
into the brain and pushes it, so GitHub holds the durable state.

## Steps
1. Fetch and prune; review what changed this session (commits, decisions, new
   capabilities).
2. CLOSE ritual — append a continuity entry to `05-logs/<date>-<topic>.md`: what
   changed, why, and evidence (links to commits/PRs/issues).
3. Update the decision board if any decision was made or changed.
4. Run the anti-drift sweep: regenerate the capabilities map and validate the docs
   mesh.
5. Update the master index and any board/issue/PR state to match reality.
6. Commit and push everything — pushing to GitHub is the durable sync.

## Done when
The continuity entry is written, the decision board and index are current, the
capabilities map and docs mesh validate, and all work is pushed.
